wikipedia_page.main: Richard Thomas Godsell (9 January 1880 – 11 April 1954) was an English cricketer. He played for Gloucestershire between 1903 and 1910. Thomas was educated at Clifton College and Trinity College, Cambridge. During World War I he was an officer in the Royal Army Service Corps.
